goals.visualization: bar chart of number of zip codes per state
goals.rationale: This will help identify which states have the highest and lowest number of zip codes and can be useful for businesses targeting specific regions.

goals.question: What is the distribution of latitude and longitude across the United States?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of latitude and longitude
goals.rationale: This will help identify the geographical spread of the zip codes and can be useful for businesses targeting specific regions.

goals.question: What is the most common city in the dataset?

goals.question: What is the distribution of counties across different states?
goals.visualization: stacked bar chart of number of counties per state
goals.rationale: This will help identify which states have the highest and lowest number of counties and can be useful for businesses targeting specific regions.

goals.question: What is the relationship between latitude and longitude?

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.countplot(x='state', data=data, order=data['state'].value_counts().index)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of zip codes across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='longitude', y='latitude', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude across the United States?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data = data.groupby('state')['county'].nunique().reset_index()
    ax = sns.barplot(x='state', y='county', data=data)
    ax.set(xlabel='State', ylabel='Number of Counties')
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of counties across different states?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
